<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-63-0780 </DOCNO><TEXT>A speech delivered at the 1987 Coal Day by the Federal Minister of Labourand Social Affairs, Federal Republic of Germany. The speaker spoke aboutthe recession in the coal industry and its social implications. Unlikeother energy sources, coal guarantees the security of future energy supplyfor Germany, therefore, long term energy policy must bear this in mind.The future of the German coal industry can only be secured by joint effortsby the government, the unions, the electricity industry and other partiesconcerned.</TEXT></DOC>